stylometry: The factors you must consider when deciding to place an order are the ordering cost which is the fixed cost everytime an order is placed.  If the orders product is produced rather then ordered then you can include the cost to set up the equipment.  Another factor is the production cost which there may be a set up cost and another production cost everytime an order is placed. The tradeoffs when deciding when to place an order are if you have backed up shelf space then you will not order as frequent and if products are flying off the shelf then orders will be placed more frequent.  Bulk ordering may be the best alternative which could lead to holding costs.
